The SMOTE is a promising oversampling method that proves its superiority in dealing with imbalanced data. It is originally introduced by Chawla, Nitesh V., et al. [96]. This technique preserves the original data without losing information, and it increases the rate of the minority class without duplication. New synthetic samples (x̂ij\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
